                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3513vg52/manifest/annotation/p4",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>to be <add>?</add> up, (however delightful the<lb/> dwelling may\n                                        be) and only meeting a congregation<lb/> on the\n                                        <add>?</add>, or be absent from home<lb/> half the year, in\n                                        order to attend divine worth of<lb/> in <add>?</add> and\n                                        endurance; I therefore am not<lb/> happy with all their\n                                        efforts to make me so.<lb/> I have noticed per Occident all\n                                        the doings<add>?</add> in<lb/> our various congregations and\n                                        read of their<lb/> zeal with much soul stirring\n                                        gratification, ho-<lb/>ping once more to be in the field of\n                                        usefulness<lb/> among them. Love to <persName>Mrs\n                                                  C</persName> tell her I expect<lb/> to find her a\n                                        happy grandma. Be kind enough<lb/> to let me know in your\n                                        next if you have<lb/> met with a <persName>Mr Joseph\n                                                  Aarons</persName>, now Physician<lb/> in\n                                                  <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>, studied <hi\n                                                  rend=\"underline\">Theology</hi> for a short<lb/>\n                                        time with <persName>Dr Raphael</persName> at <hi\n                                                  rend=\"underline\">least</hi> so he says in his<lb/>\n                                        letters, was professor at Girard College; and as I<lb/>\n                                        believe <hi rend=\"underline\">Professing</hi> many things,\n                                        and performing nothing<lb/> however this to yourself; only\n                                        let me know if you<lb/> have filled my sheet and I have\n                                        finished up<lb/> sentiments, so farewell my friend with\n                                        best<lb/> wishes for your happiness I remain</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(8)\">Yours sincerely</p>\n                              <p rend=\"indent(8)\">\n                                        <persName role=\"author\">Simha</persName>\n                              </p>\n                              <p>Grandpa's kind regard<lb/> to you, his eyes not<lb/> yet operated\n                                        on. <persName>Rachel's</persName><lb/> kind regards also</p>\n                    </body>\n          </text>\n</TEI>"
                  },
